reviewText: I kinda feel sorry for these guys n gals.  I get it, why this works for them, which is the appeal of this show, but yeah...not my thing.  Little too depressing and grotesque, honestly.
Great if you're into some pretty raunchy and raw stuff.
Interesting documentary. Worth seeing once. Wouldn't necessarily say it was worth a purchase, but I'm glad I saw it.
This is a documentary and it is ok from the point of view. For Adults only.
Some people should not go around nude and this is full of them. If you are doing this type of show you should be at least little fit. Even the subject lack any class.
It was alright I wouldn't give it 4 stars though

This maybe the worst documentary on burlesque ever; if it isn't I don't want to see the others. It is depressing to see what is involved behind the scenes. If closeups of lipstick on vaginas is your thing then, by all means, watch it, otherwise stay away.
Don't waste your time unless you enjoy very strange examples of tasteless nudity.

This is a well-made, well-presented piece. The characters take stripping to the level of performance art, appearing to use the stage as a form of therapy, and to explore some of the darker corners of the human psyche.
good intentions but no trailblazers which i believe was the intent
New burlesque still keeping original burlesque true. Great to see and know there are artist out there still doing real burlesque!
Very interesting and eye opening, well done and showed a perspective I never knew existed.
Not as good as it could have been.

Amazing documentary.. You could easily find yourself caring for the performers..We could all learn from them. The one guy is from American Horror Story (freakshow i think!) The nudity is extremely graphic..so don't watch around kids, but its worth watching.
Was not plan and filmed very good, did not  keep your interest.
Interesting insight into the artistic aspect of burlesque and somewhat sad.

Ok, this is a very interesting documentary. The subject is very intriguing and enjoyable. However, it lacks a cohesive story and the cinematography is a bit shaky. Other than that, this is a fine film to watch and learn about a fantastic American institution.

This is one of the best documentaries about some of the first artists in the neoburlesque movement. Challenging heteronormative patriarchal culture, these artists are truly special, innovators in the American style of theatre performance for the modern age. Reversing the male gaze, rejecting the gender binary, and celebrating all bodies, this documentary is amazing. But don't expect to be comfortable,  or mildly and pleasantly entertained, it's serious business and addressing serious issues that artists of this marginalized art form encounter.

I loved the honestly in this film.  The performers poured their hearts out, so I don't understand the ewwws being written here.  The neo-burlesque scene in my opinion has created a forum for true performance artists.  And I'm sorry, how can you not be in love with Rose Wood, Bob or Mat??
Eww and eww....the most unattractive group of naked people ever assembled.
This is a crazy video. It was a trip to see how some of the other half live.
Did not watch the whole thing. Not sure why even started it. Do not recommend.
